Directory listing is a feature of the `DefaultServlet` (specified as part of the Servlet Spec).

This is a Web Container feature, and as such, it cannot be controlled / edited / configured from within the WebApp itself.

But all is not lost, you&#39;ll need to deploy your web application using the Jetty XML deployable techniques, and specify an alternate `defaultsDescriptor`

&lt;!-- language: xml --&gt;

    &lt;New id=&quot;sebWebAppContext&quot;  class=&quot;org.eclipse.jetty.webapp.WebAppContext&quot;&gt;
      &lt;Set name=&quot;contextPath&quot;&gt;/sebapp&lt;/Set&gt;
      &lt;Set name=&quot;war&quot;&gt;./wars/sebapp.war&lt;/Set&gt;
      &lt;Set name=&quot;defaultsDescriptor&quot;&gt;/home/seb/jetty/sebwebdefaults.xml&lt;/Set&gt;
      .
      .
    &lt;/New&gt;

Where you take a copy of your `${jetty.home}/etc/webdefault.xml` and copy it to your location of choice (do not edit/modify/delete/change any content in the `${jetty.home}` directory).  

Set the [`dirAllowed` parameter to `false`][1].


  [1]: https://github.com/eclipse/jetty.project/blob/jetty-9.3.5.v20151012/jetty-webapp/src/main/config/etc/webdefault.xml#L143-L146

I eventually discovered that I could set this on the code base of my WebApp itself. When the web application context is setup in my java code, I can simply set it as an initiation parameter:

    WebAppContext webApp = new WebAppContext();
    webApp.setInitParameter(&quot;org.eclipse.jetty.servlet.Default.dirAllowed&quot;, &quot;false&quot;);

Your original point does not work because it cannot override the option in the webdefault.xml.  Having said that I usually just edit that file to disable listing globally for that jetty instance:
i.e.   within  webdefault.xml

    &lt;init-param&gt;
       &lt;param-name&gt;dirAllowed&lt;/param-name&gt;
       &lt;param-value&gt;false&lt;/param-value&gt;
    &lt;/init-param&gt;

